	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hi all,<br><br>Not trying to complain, but I think that maybe the quests for these spells are a little out of balance. Or maybe I'm just doing it wrong. I heard though that the luggalds in the fort in the hut drop the flicker of lava and flicker of water, so off I go to camp them.<br><br>After about 3 hours I get a flicker of lava . . .not bad. 8 hours later I still have not found a flicker of water. Last night we camped the Efreeti for 3 hours and got 2 pairs of boots and 1 Djarn's Amethist Ring. So in 3 times the amount of time it took me to get 2 boots and 1 ring from him, I still have not been able to finish a lev 44 spell quest.<br><br>Am I doing this wrong? Does the flicker of lava drop somewhere else? Or did Sony just overdo it on the effort vs. reward ratio on this quest?<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Master Reeshan Ragefire, Magus of the 57th Flame, Drinal<br>Mathurin Kerbouchard, Bard of the 36th Song, Drinal<br>Lenrok Thunderwolf, Warrior of the 37th Circle, Drinal</td></tr>
